WEBVTT

00:02.068 --> 00:03.570
[David Pomeranz performing
"Nothing's Gonna Stop Me Now"]

00:11.377 --> 00:15.048
♪ Sometimes the world
looks perfect ♪

00:15.081 --> 00:17.350
♪ Nothin' to rearrange ♪

00:17.383 --> 00:20.420
♪ Sometimes you
just get a feelin' ♪

00:20.453 --> 00:23.624
♪ Like you need
some kinda change ♪

00:24.791 --> 00:28.461
♪ No matter what
the odds are this time ♪

00:28.494 --> 00:30.731
♪ Nothing's gonna
stand in my way ♪

00:30.764 --> 00:34.200
♪ This flame in my heart
like a long lost friend ♪

00:34.234 --> 00:37.671
♪ Gives every dark street
a light at the end ♪

00:39.439 --> 00:42.342
♪ Standing tall ♪

00:42.375 --> 00:46.212
♪ On the wings of my dream ♪

00:46.246 --> 00:49.082
♪ Rise and fall ♪

00:49.115 --> 00:52.653
♪ On the wings of my dream ♪

00:52.686 --> 00:56.089
♪ The rain and thunder
the wind and haze ♪

00:56.122 --> 00:58.224
♪ I'm bound
for better days ♪

00:58.258 --> 00:59.593
♪ Oh oh ♪

00:59.626 --> 01:02.796
♪ It's my life
and my dreams ♪

01:02.829 --> 01:06.132
♪ And nothing's
gonna stop me now ♪

01:15.742 --> 01:18.211
[instrumental music]

01:23.483 --> 01:25.519
Balki, will you come on?

01:25.552 --> 01:26.787
If we don't leave
for work right now

01:26.820 --> 01:29.389
all the really good
donuts will be gone.

01:29.422 --> 01:31.725
Okay, cousin, I'm ready,
I'm ready.

01:31.758 --> 01:33.627
[telephone ringing]

01:40.333 --> 01:43.369
‐ Hello?
‐ Balki!

01:43.403 --> 01:44.270
It's for you.

01:44.304 --> 01:46.339
Well, tell them
I'll call them back later.

01:46.372 --> 01:49.375
I think it's from Mypos, I hear
chickens in the background.

01:51.778 --> 01:53.714
Nay?

01:53.747 --> 01:55.348
Uh, dazo, yaya!

01:55.381 --> 01:58.351
[speaking Myposian]

01:59.920 --> 02:02.422
‐ Who is it, your mother?
‐ No, it's my yaya!

02:03.957 --> 02:06.326
‐ Your yaya?
‐ My grandmother.

02:06.359 --> 02:07.861
‐ Oh.
‐ Balki!

02:07.894 --> 02:10.196
Uh, nay, yaya.

02:10.797 --> 02:13.767
[speaking Myposian]

02:19.573 --> 02:21.775
Okay.
Okay.

02:21.808 --> 02:23.577
Bye‐bye, babe.

02:26.379 --> 02:28.649
Cousin, the most wonderful news.

02:28.682 --> 02:31.184
My yaya is coming
to America.

02:31.217 --> 02:33.920
Well, that's great!

02:33.954 --> 02:36.790
Grandma Bartokomous
is coming to America.

02:37.824 --> 02:41.327
Get out of the city.
She's coming too?

02:42.896 --> 02:44.364
You just told me
she was coming.

02:44.397 --> 02:46.499
No. Um... no.

02:46.533 --> 02:49.235
My Yaya Bartokomous
is not coming to America.

02:49.269 --> 02:51.938
This is Yaya Biki
from my mother's side.

02:53.273 --> 02:55.308
Wait a minute,
Is this the Yaya Biki

02:55.341 --> 02:57.377
who's a 106 years old?

02:57.410 --> 03:00.814
No, this is the Yaya Biki
who has a lounge act in Vegas.

03:02.382 --> 03:04.417
What I meant was,
I‐I can't believe someone

03:04.450 --> 03:06.887
who's a 106 is gonna be
making a trip like this.

03:06.920 --> 03:08.254
Isn't it too much
for her?

03:08.288 --> 03:10.824
Well, maybe for your
average 106‐year‐old

03:10.857 --> 03:12.793
but not for my yaya.

03:12.826 --> 03:15.629
This woman, every morning
before the sun come up

03:15.662 --> 03:18.765
she takes the goats
six miles uphill to graze them

03:18.799 --> 03:20.466
then she come back
down the hill

03:20.501 --> 03:22.869
and cook breakfast
for 26 men...

03:22.903 --> 03:25.906
...then after the 26 men
go out to the fields

03:25.939 --> 03:29.442
she does 45 minutes
of low‐impact aerobics.

03:31.277 --> 03:33.814
So you see,
for someone over a hundred

03:33.847 --> 03:35.582
she's very much
an 80's woman.

03:35.616 --> 03:37.718
[chuckling]

03:37.751 --> 03:40.721
[instrumental music]

03:55.502 --> 03:57.437
[humming]

04:10.350 --> 04:11.618
[sighing]

04:15.922 --> 04:17.858
[mooing]

04:24.731 --> 04:26.667
[mooing]

04:42.849 --> 04:44.551
Balki?

04:48.889 --> 04:52.392
What can I do you for?

04:52.425 --> 04:55.962
Could we have a... chat?

05:01.802 --> 05:03.737
[mooing]

05:05.839 --> 05:07.040
Balki...

05:12.378 --> 05:14.915
When you brought
a 100 pounds of garlic

05:14.948 --> 05:17.083
into the apartment,
I said to myself,

05:17.117 --> 05:21.487
"Okay... so Yaya Biki
loves scampi."

05:23.990 --> 05:26.860
When you told me
she likes to keep fresh eels

05:26.893 --> 05:28.929
in the bathtub,

05:28.962 --> 05:32.498
I said to myself,
"Hey... no problem.

05:33.399 --> 05:35.001
I take showers."

05:38.171 --> 05:40.674
‐ But‐‐
‐ It's the cow, isn't it?

05:45.612 --> 05:47.781
Well, yes.

05:47.814 --> 05:49.382
The cow...

05:53.520 --> 05:55.722
...bothers me.

06:00.060 --> 06:02.462
I want Yaya Biki
to feel at home

06:02.495 --> 06:04.130
I really do!

06:04.164 --> 06:07.133
But have you ever thought that
she'd like to see how we live?

06:07.167 --> 06:09.670
Experience the American way
of living?

06:09.703 --> 06:12.739
Things like, oh... uh,
I don't know, uh, jeez

06:12.773 --> 06:14.040
what example
can I think of?

06:14.074 --> 06:16.743
Uh... oh!

06:16.777 --> 06:19.780
Beef on the table
instead of beef at the table?

06:21.948 --> 06:23.884
[mooing]

06:31.725 --> 06:33.393
Sorry.

06:36.763 --> 06:38.064
Please...

06:38.098 --> 06:41.835
...can we get rid
of the cow?

06:41.868 --> 06:44.771
Well, cousin, I'm just
trying to give Yaya Biki

06:44.805 --> 06:47.874
a few of the little
comforts of home.

06:49.543 --> 06:52.513
See? Look,
I made her this blanket.

06:52.546 --> 06:54.915
I weave it myself
so that she won't get cold

06:54.948 --> 06:57.450
while she's watching
"Letterman."

06:58.852 --> 07:01.922
‐ It's beautiful.
‐ How about that chair?

07:01.955 --> 07:05.158
That chair is just like the one
she has on Mypos.

07:08.962 --> 07:11.665
Look, I don't mind
the chair.

07:11.698 --> 07:14.100
I mind the cow.

07:15.702 --> 07:18.471
Please... let's take it back?

07:20.941 --> 07:23.644
We can take it back,
can't we?

07:25.546 --> 07:28.815
Okay, we can 86 the cow.

07:28.849 --> 07:31.752
She's just a rental.

07:31.785 --> 07:34.755
Good, I'll go change clothes.

07:34.788 --> 07:37.591
Ah, cousin,
before you go, um...

07:37.624 --> 07:39.693
...you ought to know
that there may be a penalty

07:39.726 --> 07:42.529
for returning her unmilked.

07:46.299 --> 07:48.835
I'll chance it.

07:48.869 --> 07:51.805
[instrumental music]

08:01.147 --> 08:03.817
[all singing "She's A Jolly
Good Fellow" in Myposian]

08:03.850 --> 08:07.654
♪ Ipepita irinki
halla hop chop yop yop ♪

08:07.688 --> 08:11.558
♪ Ipepita irinki
halla hop chop yop yop ♪

08:11.592 --> 08:13.259
♪ Ipepita irinki ♪

08:13.293 --> 08:16.563
♪ Halla hop chop yop yop ♪

08:17.263 --> 08:20.133
♪ Aynel ♪

08:20.166 --> 08:22.869
♪ Och viddi voy poy ♪

08:22.903 --> 08:26.139
♪ Dimina babbasticki ♪

08:34.047 --> 08:36.549
Very good.

08:36.582 --> 08:38.284
I think
"For She's A Jolly Good Fellow"

08:38.318 --> 08:40.621
really works in Myposian.

08:41.187 --> 08:42.188
Don't you?

08:42.222 --> 08:44.324
Oh, real toe tapper

08:44.357 --> 08:45.526
Okay, now, um...

08:45.559 --> 08:49.029
...everybody please be at
the apartment at seven o'clock

08:49.062 --> 08:51.231
so that when Cousin Larry
and I arrive with Yaya Biki

08:51.264 --> 08:53.033
you can jump out
and yell "surprise!"

08:53.066 --> 08:54.801
Wait, wait,
hold on, honey.

08:54.835 --> 08:56.637
You sure it's such
a good idea to jump out

08:56.670 --> 08:58.972
and yell at a woman
who's a 106?

09:00.206 --> 09:01.207
No problem.

09:01.241 --> 09:04.845
Yaya Biki is as strong
as a sea turtle.

09:04.878 --> 09:06.179
Of course,
she has better legs.

09:06.212 --> 09:08.181
Now, I got to run.

09:08.214 --> 09:11.652
I got to pick up party hats
and half a pound of head cheese.

09:11.685 --> 09:14.220
And listen, don't forget
to bring your dancing feet.

09:14.254 --> 09:16.256
Yaya Biki loves
to party down.

09:17.724 --> 09:18.892
A hundred and six

09:18.925 --> 09:21.361
and as strong as a sea turtle.

09:21.394 --> 09:23.697
I wonder what I'll be like
when I'm old.

09:23.730 --> 09:26.266
Probably a lot like
Yaya Biki.

09:26.299 --> 09:29.202
Why, Harriette, you think so?

09:29.235 --> 09:30.804
Sure I do, honey.

09:30.837 --> 09:34.274
You're already startin'
to look like a sea turtle.

09:34.307 --> 09:35.842
[telephone ringing]

09:35.876 --> 09:36.877
I'll get that.

09:36.910 --> 09:38.845
[chuckling]

09:40.013 --> 09:41.982
Hello?

09:42.015 --> 09:45.652
No, Mr. Bartokomous
is gone for the day.

09:45.686 --> 09:47.754
Well, uh, if it's important,
I can take a message.

09:47.788 --> 09:48.989
I'm his cousin.

09:53.293 --> 09:55.228
Oh, no.

09:58.732 --> 10:00.701
Yeah. I‐I‐I understand.

10:00.734 --> 10:03.036
Uh... thank you.

10:04.905 --> 10:06.272
Goodbye.

10:07.207 --> 10:10.143
Larry?
W‐what's wrong?

10:10.176 --> 10:12.345
That was the airline.

10:12.378 --> 10:13.647
Yaya Biki got off

10:13.680 --> 10:16.683
to change planes in New York
and, uh...

10:16.717 --> 10:18.852
...her heart stopped.

10:18.885 --> 10:20.754
She's dead.

10:20.787 --> 10:23.757
[instrumental music]

10:30.130 --> 10:32.899
[instrumental music]

10:38.438 --> 10:40.941
‐ Jennifer...
‐ Oh!

10:42.242 --> 10:44.978
Are you sure we have
enough potato chips?

10:45.011 --> 10:46.847
Balki, you already
bought 15 bags

10:46.880 --> 10:49.950
and we only have
10 people coming.

10:49.983 --> 10:52.786
You're right,
maybe we do need more.

10:54.220 --> 10:57.724
Cousin! Cousin, look!
Look, look what we did!

10:57.758 --> 10:59.092
Does this say

10:59.125 --> 11:01.695
"Welcome to America"
or what?

11:01.728 --> 11:03.396
[chuckling]

11:03.429 --> 11:05.131
Well, yes, it does.

11:05.165 --> 11:07.433
When Yaya Biki sees all this,
she's gonna die.

11:11.437 --> 11:13.840
Uh, Jennifer and Mary Anne

11:13.874 --> 11:15.341
don't you need
to hurry upstairs

11:15.375 --> 11:17.277
and change for the party?

11:17.310 --> 11:20.046
Larry, we have changed
for the party.

11:21.047 --> 11:23.016
And lovely you are too.

11:24.150 --> 11:26.186
Uh... I don't know
how to tell you this

11:26.219 --> 11:28.989
but Lydia is wearing
that exact same dress.

11:29.022 --> 11:32.458
‐ Uh, but if you don't mind...
‐ Oh, no, no, I'll change.

11:32.492 --> 11:34.394
Uh, Mary Anne, did I mention
that Harriette is wearing

11:34.427 --> 11:36.429
what you have on?

11:39.165 --> 11:41.334
Wow, small world.

11:42.536 --> 11:43.904
I better change.

11:43.937 --> 11:45.806
Uh, cousin...

11:45.839 --> 11:47.874
...is 15 bags
of potato chips enough?

11:47.908 --> 11:49.042
We have ten guests coming,

11:49.075 --> 11:51.745
I made four gallons
of sheep dip.

11:52.846 --> 11:54.815
Balki... sit down.

11:56.216 --> 11:57.317
Okay.

11:57.350 --> 11:59.252
I guess I could
take a break.

11:59.285 --> 12:00.921
I have been running around

12:00.954 --> 12:04.224
like a chicken with
his head glued on all day.

12:07.293 --> 12:09.462
Balki, the airline called.

12:09.495 --> 12:11.231
Yaya Biki is...

12:13.466 --> 12:16.136
...is going to be late.

12:18.104 --> 12:19.740
How late?

12:20.240 --> 12:23.109
A lot.

12:23.143 --> 12:25.078
Cousin, what is it?

12:25.111 --> 12:27.180
Yaya Biki...

12:27.213 --> 12:29.850
...is not coming.

12:30.450 --> 12:32.118
Something happened.

12:34.387 --> 12:37.457
[gasping]
She bought the farm, didn't she?

12:38.458 --> 12:40.493
Well, yes, she did.

12:41.394 --> 12:44.965
Oh!
Oh, this is wonderful!

12:44.998 --> 12:47.901
She's always
wanted that farm.

12:50.136 --> 12:51.838
Of course,
she can't come now

12:51.872 --> 12:54.007
she's got to go out
and buy sheep and goats and...

12:54.040 --> 12:56.242
‐ No, no, Balki, Balki.
‐ ...I don't know what all.

12:56.276 --> 12:59.479
Balki, "Bought the farm"
is an expression.

13:01.247 --> 13:04.417
Well, of course it is,
don't be ridiculous.

13:06.419 --> 13:09.122
What does it mean?

13:09.155 --> 13:12.092
I know this is gonna come
as a terrible shock...

13:12.125 --> 13:13.126
...but...

13:13.159 --> 13:14.460
...Yaya Biki got off

13:14.494 --> 13:16.863
the plane in New York...

13:16.897 --> 13:19.432
...and died.

13:29.576 --> 13:32.613
Okay, so we got
ten guests coming.

13:32.646 --> 13:35.616
Fifteen bags
of potato chips enough?

13:35.649 --> 13:37.183
Balki, did you understand
what I said?

13:37.217 --> 13:40.420
Yes, you said
Yaya Biki is dead.

13:40.453 --> 13:43.389
But that don't solve
the chip problem.

13:45.058 --> 13:46.292
Oh, oh, where are you going?

13:46.326 --> 13:48.562
I'm gonna go out
and buy some more potato chips.

13:48.595 --> 13:51.965
If we run out of munchies,
this party's gonna be a dud.

13:51.998 --> 13:54.935
[instrumental music]

13:55.468 --> 13:56.870
[door closing]

14:10.517 --> 14:12.018
Cousin...

14:12.052 --> 14:14.921
...wasn't that
the best circus you ever see?

14:14.955 --> 14:17.490
How about that Joko
The Human Fireball?

14:17.524 --> 14:19.359
What an entertainer.

14:19.392 --> 14:22.228
I just hope they got him
to the hospital okay.

14:22.262 --> 14:23.463
‐ Balki‐‐
‐ Uh...

14:23.496 --> 14:25.666
The‐the daring young man
on the flying trapeze...

14:25.699 --> 14:27.200
What kind of a person

14:27.233 --> 14:29.335
would climb 25 feet
up in the air

14:29.369 --> 14:32.438
then just drop off
and then swing back

14:32.472 --> 14:35.341
and forth
and back and forth

14:35.375 --> 14:38.444
and then just
hand himself to somebody?

14:38.478 --> 14:40.113
[squeaking]

14:43.584 --> 14:47.554
Cousin, cousin, I have
a storm in my brain.

14:47.588 --> 14:50.290
Why don't we
invite the girls down

14:50.323 --> 14:52.559
and rent a movie
and get ourselves a pizza‐‐

14:52.593 --> 14:53.627
Balki, Balki, Balki...

14:53.660 --> 14:56.462
...why don't you give the girls
and me a night off?

14:56.496 --> 14:57.531
For the past three weeks

14:57.564 --> 14:59.566
you‐you've dragged us around
to every amusement park

14:59.600 --> 15:02.969
zoo, movie and video arcade
in Chicago.

15:03.003 --> 15:06.640
Well, excuse me
for being fun.

15:06.673 --> 15:08.975
[blowing whistle]

15:10.276 --> 15:11.978
[squeaking]

15:15.048 --> 15:16.249
[squeaking]

15:21.387 --> 15:23.023
Okay, I know.

15:23.056 --> 15:25.225
I'll make some popcorn
and we can practice catching it

15:25.258 --> 15:27.193
in our mouths.

15:27.227 --> 15:28.629
Balki, Balki

15:28.662 --> 15:30.230
this is Cousin Larry.

15:30.263 --> 15:31.698
You don't have to do this.

15:31.732 --> 15:34.601
No, cousin, it's no bother.
I love making popcorn.

15:34.635 --> 15:36.570
No, no, not that.

15:38.138 --> 15:40.473
I mean, you don't have
to pretend

15:40.507 --> 15:42.509
you're happy around me.

15:42.543 --> 15:43.977
What are you talking about?

15:44.010 --> 15:45.512
I'm happy.

15:45.546 --> 15:46.747
You're not happy.

15:46.780 --> 15:49.149
‐ I am happy.
‐ No, you're not.

15:49.182 --> 15:50.717
‐ I'm happy!
‐ No, you're not.

15:50.751 --> 15:53.720
‐ I'm happy.
‐ No, you're not.

15:54.688 --> 15:56.523
I'm happy.

15:58.024 --> 15:59.726
Now let it go.

16:01.795 --> 16:04.531
Okay, fine.
You're happy.

16:04.565 --> 16:06.600
Your yaya dies
and you're happy.

16:06.633 --> 16:08.635
It makes perfect sense.

16:10.470 --> 16:13.473
Okay, cousin,
I'm not happy.

16:15.475 --> 16:17.443
Let me explain
something to you.

16:18.745 --> 16:21.281
I've been prepared
for this.

16:21.314 --> 16:23.617
On Yaya Biki's 100th birthday

16:23.650 --> 16:26.319
she pulled me aside,
she said, "Balki...

16:26.352 --> 16:28.722
...today, I am 100 years old.

16:28.755 --> 16:32.192
Chances are I'm not going
to make another hundred.

16:35.461 --> 16:38.331
So when I go,

16:38.364 --> 16:41.201
please just go on
with your life

16:41.234 --> 16:43.036
as if nothing happened.

16:43.069 --> 16:46.573
Please, promise me this
so that I can rest in peace."

16:46.607 --> 16:48.374
I promised her that

16:48.408 --> 16:50.443
and that's all
there is to it.

16:50.777 --> 16:51.845
Well...

16:51.878 --> 16:55.181
Well, you're not going on
as if nothing has happened.

16:55.215 --> 16:56.449
You're doing happy things

16:56.482 --> 16:58.719
but I can see
you're hurting inside

16:58.752 --> 17:00.120
and you're trying to hide it.

17:00.153 --> 17:01.555
You can't hide it from me,
Balki.

17:01.588 --> 17:02.589
I know you too well.

17:02.623 --> 17:04.691
Cousin,
I'm trying to do

17:04.724 --> 17:07.359
what I promised Yaya Biki
I would do.

17:08.762 --> 17:11.164
Yaya Biki was very wise.

17:11.196 --> 17:14.734
And I'm sure she wanted
to make things easier for you.

17:14.768 --> 17:15.801
But if she could see you now

17:15.836 --> 17:18.371
she'd say she made a mistake.

17:19.640 --> 17:21.808
When someone close to you dies

17:21.842 --> 17:23.476
you have to mourn for them.

17:23.510 --> 17:25.145
No.

17:25.178 --> 17:27.146
No, no.

17:28.414 --> 17:30.350
[sighing]

17:35.789 --> 17:39.392
I had an uncle
whose wife died

17:39.425 --> 17:42.362
and he had a very
hard time getting over it.

17:44.497 --> 17:46.667
He held things in...

17:47.768 --> 17:50.236
...but the poor guy
was a wreck.

17:50.904 --> 17:52.506
So he tried something.

17:52.539 --> 17:53.507
[Balki sighing]

17:53.540 --> 17:55.709
He wrote a letter
to his wife

17:55.742 --> 17:57.110
telling her all the things

17:57.143 --> 17:59.445
he wished
he could say to her.

18:00.647 --> 18:03.083
And did this make
everything better?

18:04.217 --> 18:07.588
Well... it made things
a little better.

18:09.656 --> 18:11.157
But if you don't
wanna write to her

18:11.191 --> 18:12.793
try talking to her.

18:12.826 --> 18:14.561
It, it doesn't matter
what you do.

18:14.595 --> 18:17.698
The important thing is
to get it out, to...

18:19.733 --> 18:21.768
...to say goodbye.

18:23.336 --> 18:25.706
I don't want
to say goodbye.

18:28.742 --> 18:30.443
Well...

18:30.476 --> 18:33.246
...I'm only trying to help.

18:34.715 --> 18:36.917
I'm gonna go upstairs
and, uh, tell the girls

18:36.950 --> 18:38.284
they don't have to
come down tonight

18:38.318 --> 18:40.186
and watch you be happy.

18:53.567 --> 18:54.668
[door closing]

18:55.569 --> 18:57.203
What, what...

18:58.471 --> 19:00.173
[sighing]

19:11.618 --> 19:12.819
[sighing]

19:12.853 --> 19:14.655
Well, yaya, here we are.

19:14.688 --> 19:17.323
Oh, what the...

19:17.357 --> 19:18.759
[sighing]

19:20.360 --> 19:21.494
[sighing]

19:23.396 --> 19:26.366
[instrumental music]

19:43.383 --> 19:44.685
[sighing]

19:45.752 --> 19:47.521
Yaya...

19:49.389 --> 19:51.525
...here I am...

19:51.558 --> 19:53.994
...in America...

19:54.027 --> 19:56.329
...just where you
wanted me to be.

19:57.664 --> 19:59.633
I...

19:59.666 --> 20:03.236
I know it was your dream
to come here too.

20:03.269 --> 20:06.306
I just wish you could've seen
more of this country.

20:08.542 --> 20:10.977
I was thinking...

20:11.011 --> 20:13.947
...maybe you saw
the Statue of Liberty

20:13.980 --> 20:16.650
from the window
of your airplane.

20:18.384 --> 20:19.953
Wasn't she beautiful?

20:22.055 --> 20:23.757
I remember...

20:23.790 --> 20:27.293
...the first time
I ever saw her.

20:27.327 --> 20:31.031
I was, I was sailing
into New York Harbor

20:31.064 --> 20:32.899
